page.title: 17LALEHAM SCHOOL FIELD_PART 2
page.content: All the plants mentioned on the previous page (i.e.page 16_{Laleham {School Field_Flora})as well as Red and White Deadnettle,Cow Parsley,Poppies, Thistles,Nettles,Wild Pea,Common Mallow and Creeping Cinqfoil are to be found in the wild area.Here too,logs from the old oak tree felled in 1981,harbour fungi,woodlice,snails and hunting spiders.Web spiders set their traps in bushes whilst the nettles encourage butterflies;Peacock,Tortoise _shell,Comma and Cinnebar have been studied there. A House Martin annually nests high against the school wall and Starlings, Sparrows,Blackbirds,Robins,Swifts,Blue and Great Tits,Greenfinches,Chaffinches,Collared Doves,Crows,Rooks,Magpies and Mallard Ducks are amongst our regular visitors.
